  "text": "Once the parameters maintenance is made, foreground/background detection can be made and so on. The background model is then the first components (in order of highest to lowest , / , ), whose weight is above the threshold. Higher-rank components have low variances and high probabilities, which are typical characteristics of background. The component is the maximum number of components in the background model and reflects the number of modes we expect in the background probability distribution function. Pixels that do not match any components determined to be in the background model are considered to be foreground [CITATION_1] . Figure 4 shows the process of background and foreground detection using MoG.",
